==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: critical temperature
<hw>crit"ic*al tem"per*a*ture</hw> <fld>(Physics)</fld>, <def>A certain
temperature, different for different gases, but always the same for each
gas, regarded as the temperature above which no amount of pressure can
produce condensation to a liquid; the temperature above which a gas
cannot be liquified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Criticaster</ent>⟦br⟧
